Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.08,0:00:04.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Today we’ll talk about everybody’s favorite topic, death.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.08,0:00:04.39,CHN,,0,0,0,,今天我们会谈及大家最爱的话题：死亡
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.39,0:00:08.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,You probably expect to live up to your life expectancy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.39,0:00:08.26,CHN,,0,0,0,,你可能会预计  你能活到比自己的预期寿命更长  对吗
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:11.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,No wrong. You’ll probably live longer than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.27,0:00:11.44,CHN,,0,0,0,,没错  你很有可能活得更久
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:15.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,This graph shows the probability of death at a certain age.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.44,0:00:15.31,CHN,,0,0,0,,这张柱状图显示了在某个年龄段死亡的概率
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,The red line here is the mean value, that’s the average age of death
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.31,0:00:18.93,CHN,,0,0,0,,这里的红线是死亡年龄的平均值
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.93,0:00:21.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,and what’s normally called life expectancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.93,0:00:21.57,CHN,,0,0,0,,一般称之为“预期寿命”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:25.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,In first world countries it’s typically early 80s.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.57,0:00:25.06,CHN,,0,0,0,,在老牌发达国家  预期寿命一般略高于80岁
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.05,0:00:29.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Though the age at which most people die is higher, that’s the median.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.05,0:00:29.35,CHN,,0,0,0,,但更多人的死亡岁数要比均值更大  这也是中位数
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:30.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,But unless you’re a newborn,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:30.84,CHN,,0,0,0,,不过  只要你不是刚出生
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:34.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,the mean value of the entire graph isn’t relevant for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.84,0:00:34.53,CHN,,0,0,0,,整个图表的平均值就跟你无关
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.53,0:00:36.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you survived the first year of your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.53,0:00:36.93,CHN,,0,0,0,,如果你活到满一周岁了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:42.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,you’d instead take the mean of the {\b1}remaining{\b0} years which is at somewhat higher age.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:42.41,CHN,,0,0,0,,你应当只用剩余的（也就是更大的）年龄来计算平均值
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.41,0:00:45.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now we repeat this for all further ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.41,0:00:45.38,CHN,,0,0,0,,你不断长大变老时也重复这样的计算
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:47.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,As you see, the older you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.38,0:00:47.21,CHN,,0,0,0,,如你所见 你的年龄越大
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.21,0:00:51.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,the further the mean of the {\b1}remaining years{\b0} moves higher ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.21,0:00:51.50,CHN,,0,0,0,,剩余年龄的平均值就会越靠右
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.50,0:00:53.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,This leads to the odd conclusion that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.50,0:00:53.71,CHN,,0,0,0,,这就会导致一个奇怪的结论{\fsp-30}：
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:00:56.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,if you’ve reached the age of your life expectancy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:00:56.34,CHN,,0,0,0,,你如果达到了预期寿命
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:00:59.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,you can actually expect to live another 8-10 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.34,0:00:59.76,CHN,,0,0,0,,反而可以估计  自己还能再活个十年八年
